issue.title: Progress
issue.body:
Progress beyond what was developed and presented at Hack the North. Not without its share of issues but much more coherent and consolidated than something that was thrown together over almost 36 sleepless hours using copious amounts of Red Bull and coffee while dealing with missing mission-critical hardware (go figure).

Summary of work done:
![fzbrebj](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1712054/10154771/8ee41b36-6639-11e5-9e70-ef6107fa9e23.jpg)

issue.title: Dynamic script execution on Ajax-loaded pages
issue.body:
Currently, when the JS in the footer receives an HTML document from the server via Ajax and performs a replacement, and the scripts in the retrieved document don't execute (this is well-defined, normal behaviour).

Possible solution: [**On-demand Javascript**](http://ajaxpatterns.org/archive/On-Demand_Javascript.php)

issue.title: Remove `ngrok` dependency
issue.body:
`ngrok` was put in place to serve as a sort of dynamic IP thing to save time setting up an actual server at Hack the North. This should no longer be necessary, and code should be amended to work without needing `ngrok` at any point.

This will also remove an ugly binary blob from the repository.

issue.title: Fix integration with Twilio
issue.body: Currently, Twilio servers throw errors when sent a properly-formatted text (generated by the toy android app included in this repo). These errors are an apparent result of bad communication between Twilio middleware and the Tornado backend.
